WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:04.003
♪♪

00:04.963 --> 00:07.340
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.424 --> 00:10.844
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-own ♪

00:10.927 --> 00:12.262
♪ Outside we look different ♪

00:12.345 --> 00:13.888
♪ Inside we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.972 --> 00:16.182
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.266 --> 00:18.518
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.601 --> 00:21.771
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-ou ♪

00:21.855 --> 00:23.606
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.690 --> 00:25.150
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:25.233 --> 00:28.027
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:29.612 --> 00:34.701
♪♪

00:34.784 --> 00:38.371
[ School bell rings ]
Okay, class,
so this one is a circle,

00:38.455 --> 00:40.457
and this one is a...

00:40.540 --> 00:41.750
square.

00:41.833 --> 00:42.959
Teacher Terry!

00:43.042 --> 00:44.919
I don't want to
turn in my homework.

00:45.003 --> 00:46.129
Why not?

00:46.212 --> 00:48.631
Because I don't want to
be judged.

00:48.715 --> 00:49.966
Teacher Terry!

00:50.049 --> 00:52.469
Did you know there's music
in<i> everything?</i>

00:52.552 --> 00:54.637
Music in my pencil,
music in my desk,

00:54.721 --> 00:55.972
music in Mertha.

00:56.055 --> 00:57.932
-Quit it!
-Teacher Terry.

00:58.016 --> 01:00.518
I'm here for a progress report
on my daughter.

01:00.602 --> 01:03.146
-Me?
-No, not you, sweetie.

01:03.229 --> 01:04.522
Claudette.

01:04.606 --> 01:07.066
Have you been giving her
extra homework like I asked?

01:07.150 --> 01:10.028
Holk got stuck in
the pencil sharpener again.

01:10.111 --> 01:11.321
Uhhh...

01:11.404 --> 01:13.448
[ Groans ]

01:15.533 --> 01:17.911
Seth?
What are you doing here?

01:17.994 --> 01:19.996
I didn't get to ask
these questions in class.

01:20.079 --> 01:21.164
Got a minute?

01:21.247 --> 01:23.583
Can't this wait
until tomorrow?

01:23.666 --> 01:26.169
Is it not the responsibility
of the state

01:26.252 --> 01:28.379
to provide me
with an education?

01:28.463 --> 01:29.714
[ Groans ]

01:29.798 --> 01:32.217
Ahem.
Question the first...

01:32.300 --> 01:35.595
♪♪

01:35.678 --> 01:36.679
[ Sighs ]

01:36.763 --> 01:38.640
[ Groans ]

01:38.723 --> 01:41.643
Man:<i> And now, back to</i>
<i>"Fungspiracy Theories."</i>

01:41.726 --> 01:43.436
<i>The moon --</i>
<i>a round friend,</i>

01:43.520 --> 01:45.021
<i>or just a made-up hoax?</i>

01:45.104 --> 01:46.856
<i>Tonight we investigate.</i>

01:46.940 --> 01:49.609
[ Knock on door ]

01:49.692 --> 01:51.528
Mr. Mayor?
Teacher Terry!

01:51.611 --> 01:53.696
In recognition of
all your hard work,

01:53.780 --> 01:55.114
I'm giving you...

01:55.198 --> 01:58.076
more responsibilities!

01:58.159 --> 01:59.744
But I --

01:59.828 --> 02:02.539
First I need you to grade
<i>all</i> these standardized tests.

02:02.622 --> 02:04.207
Do I get overtime
for this?

02:04.290 --> 02:06.709
[ Laughs ]

02:09.170 --> 02:10.672
Ugh.

02:10.755 --> 02:12.257
[ Rooster crows ]

02:12.340 --> 02:15.260
[ Snoring ]
Hmm?

02:17.804 --> 02:20.598
[ Indistinct talking ]

02:20.682 --> 02:22.058
What ya got there, Seth?

02:22.141 --> 02:24.561
Why, more questions for
Teacher Terry, of course.

02:24.644 --> 02:26.062
They came to me
in my dreams.

02:26.145 --> 02:29.482
[ School bell rings ]
Okay, quiet down everyone.

02:29.566 --> 02:30.775
Coach Croach?

02:30.859 --> 02:32.277
Where's Teacher Terry?

02:32.360 --> 02:34.112
Is she sick?
Is she alive?

02:34.195 --> 02:35.738
[ Sobs ]

02:35.822 --> 02:38.616
Teacher Terry took
a personal day.

02:38.700 --> 02:41.411
Sometimes grownups
get stressed out,

02:41.494 --> 02:43.580
and they need to relax
so they don't, like,

02:43.663 --> 02:45.748
flip out and quit forever.

02:45.832 --> 02:50.169
Anywho, says you're learning
about pentagons.

02:50.253 --> 02:52.005
That's not it.

02:52.088 --> 02:53.131
Alright, hang on!

02:53.214 --> 02:55.091
Do you think
she'd really quit?

02:55.174 --> 02:56.509
This is<i> your</i> fault.

02:56.593 --> 02:58.803
Your mom is
always hovering.

02:59.804 --> 03:03.057
Holk's the one always
getting stuck in things.

03:03.141 --> 03:04.309
Ugh! Ugh.

03:04.392 --> 03:06.227
We can't blame
each other.

03:06.311 --> 03:07.937
Besides,
Seth is the worst.

03:08.021 --> 03:10.273
Ah-bup-bup!
Blame is not important.

03:10.356 --> 03:13.776
What Teacher Terry needs
is the most relaxing day ever

03:13.860 --> 03:15.862
so that she never
leaves us.

03:15.945 --> 03:17.447
If you love someone truly,

03:17.530 --> 03:20.199
you gotta grab on for dear life
and never let them go.

03:20.283 --> 03:21.451
Works for me.

03:21.534 --> 03:23.953
Okay, so it's --
it's five sides.

03:24.037 --> 03:26.873
It's fi-- okay.

03:28.082 --> 03:29.250
Seth:
Alright everyone,

03:29.334 --> 03:31.085
it's time to
check on teacher.

03:31.169 --> 03:32.712
Holk, if you will.

03:32.795 --> 03:35.048
Eee-hah!

03:35.131 --> 03:36.591
[ Glass squeaking ]

03:36.674 --> 03:39.969
[ Sobbing ]

03:40.053 --> 03:41.429
[ Whistle! ]

03:41.512 --> 03:43.306
She isn't relaxing
at all.

03:43.389 --> 03:45.892
Maybe we could teach her
some breathing techniques?

03:45.975 --> 03:48.102
Well,<i> we're</i> the ones
stressing her out.

03:48.186 --> 03:50.980
We'll help her relax
secretly.

03:53.441 --> 03:54.692
Come on!

03:54.776 --> 03:56.945
All: Yeah!
[ Giggling ]

03:57.028 --> 03:58.780
Alright, Holk,
once more.

03:58.863 --> 03:59.989
Huah-ah!

04:00.073 --> 04:01.199
[ Grunts ]

04:01.282 --> 04:02.325
Ow!

04:02.408 --> 04:05.161
Hey!
There's no one to throw me.

04:05.244 --> 04:06.579
Holk sad.

04:06.663 --> 04:08.081
Guard the apartment.

04:08.164 --> 04:10.458
Make sure nothing stressful
gets near Teacher Terry.

04:10.541 --> 04:12.293
Holk happy!

04:12.377 --> 04:14.754
[ Laughs ] Raaah!

04:14.837 --> 04:15.964
Raah!

04:20.259 --> 04:23.012
Wow, Teacher Terry's apartment
is very...

04:23.096 --> 04:24.263
lived in.

04:24.347 --> 04:27.392
One misplaced footstep
could blow our cover.

04:27.475 --> 04:29.727
I'll be quiet
like a ghost.

04:29.811 --> 04:31.479
Ha, ha, ha, ha.
[ Grunts ]

04:31.562 --> 04:33.356
Ooh. Ooh. Ah!

04:33.439 --> 04:34.440
Huh?

04:34.524 --> 04:35.858
[ All gasping ]

04:35.942 --> 04:38.695
Ugh.
Just my dirty apartment.

04:38.778 --> 04:41.781
I wish this mess
would clean itself.

04:41.864 --> 04:43.992
Hey. That's something
we could do.

04:44.075 --> 04:45.702
Start cleaning.

04:45.785 --> 04:48.705
♪♪

04:48.788 --> 04:51.499
Whoa! Ah, ah, ahhh!

04:51.582 --> 04:58.798
♪♪

04:58.881 --> 05:00.133
[ Sparkle! ]

05:00.216 --> 05:01.551
[ Grunts ]

05:01.634 --> 05:03.845
Ah! Ah! Aah!

05:03.928 --> 05:06.723
Mm? Huh?

05:06.806 --> 05:10.226
Ya know, it's not
<i>that</i> messy in here.

05:10.310 --> 05:13.187
My stress must've
made things look worse.

05:13.271 --> 05:15.898
I should unwind
with a hot bath.

05:15.982 --> 05:17.608
Oh, no, the bathroom!

05:17.692 --> 05:19.652
Go, go, go, go, go!

05:22.405 --> 05:24.907
Whoa!
[ Laughs ]

05:24.991 --> 05:28.494
You know, I have
a<i> really</i> nice bathroom.

05:28.578 --> 05:31.247
[ Relaxing music plays ]

05:31.330 --> 05:33.833
♪♪

05:33.916 --> 05:35.752
Relaxation.

05:37.170 --> 05:39.047
Waterfalls.

05:40.548 --> 05:42.717
The ocean.

05:44.427 --> 05:47.138
Waterfalls again.

05:49.849 --> 05:51.726
Ahhhh!

05:51.809 --> 05:54.604
That bath really did the trick.

05:54.687 --> 05:57.023
There's more where
that came from.

05:57.106 --> 05:58.608
I wonder what's on TV.

05:58.691 --> 06:01.444
Man:<i> And now back to</i>
<i>"Fungspiracy Theories."</i>

06:01.527 --> 06:03.988
<i>Can dinosaurs communicate</i>
<i>with clouds?</i>

06:04.072 --> 06:05.990
<i>We'll give you</i>
<i>the frightening answer.</i>

06:06.074 --> 06:09.410
<i>But first --</i>
<i>is someone out to get you?</i>

06:09.494 --> 06:11.162
Oh, yeah, this'll be good.

06:11.245 --> 06:14.999
Man:<i> Sign number one -- objects</i>
<i>mysteriously disappearing</i>

06:15.083 --> 06:17.126
<i>and reappearing around you.</i>

06:17.210 --> 06:19.045
[ Water pouring ]

06:19.128 --> 06:20.088
Ah!

06:20.171 --> 06:21.089
Hee-hee.

06:21.172 --> 06:22.548
Man:<i> Sign number two --</i>

06:22.632 --> 06:26.135
<i>people around you</i>
<i>acting strange.</i>

06:26.219 --> 06:28.471
Ah! Whoo! Whoo!

06:28.554 --> 06:29.555
Ah! Uh!

06:29.639 --> 06:31.641
Okay,
that's a little strange.

06:31.724 --> 06:33.309
You leave
my teacher alone.

06:33.392 --> 06:35.311
Okay, okay, I'm sorry!

06:35.394 --> 06:36.979
Man:<i> Sign number three --</i>

06:37.063 --> 06:40.858
<i>the whispers of unseen voices</i>
<i>plotting against you.</i>

06:40.942 --> 06:43.319
I wanna paint
Teacher Terry's fingernails.

06:43.402 --> 06:45.196
I'll cook Teacher Terry
dinner.

06:45.279 --> 06:46.656
[ Whispering ] Teacher Terry.
Teacher Terry.

06:46.739 --> 06:49.158
[ Gasps ]
The world<i> is</i> out to get me!

06:49.242 --> 06:51.119
Man:
<i>Remember -- remain calm.</i>

06:51.202 --> 06:53.037
<i>Don't let them know</i>
<i>you're on to them.</i>

06:53.121 --> 06:57.333
<i>Get to a safe location</i>
<i>and change your whole identity.</i>

06:57.416 --> 07:00.086
Alright, stay calm.

07:00.169 --> 07:01.546
What a nice, relaxing day.

07:01.629 --> 07:05.091
So glad no one's
plotting against me.

07:05.174 --> 07:08.302
I think I might just
call it a night.

07:08.386 --> 07:09.387
[ Sparkle! ]

07:09.470 --> 07:10.888
[ Gasps and whimpers ]

07:10.972 --> 07:13.141
Okay, I'm sleeping now!

07:13.224 --> 07:16.435
[ Snores loudly ]

07:16.519 --> 07:19.230
[ Laughing ]

07:21.983 --> 07:23.317
[ Whistle! ]

07:23.401 --> 07:25.278
Teacher's sleeping
like a baby.

07:25.361 --> 07:29.490
Thanks to us she'll be clean,
refreshed, awake,

07:29.574 --> 07:31.200
and ready for class
tomorrow

07:31.284 --> 07:32.660
without a bit of stress.

07:32.743 --> 07:36.038
Ha! You're not getting me,
ya stinkin' conspirators.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.165
[ Panting ]

07:37.248 --> 07:38.499
I'm gone forever!

07:38.583 --> 07:39.834
[ Laughing wildly ]

07:39.917 --> 07:42.044
I think she's still
a tad stressed out.

07:42.128 --> 07:43.212
We gotta stop her.

07:43.296 --> 07:44.547
Hello, children.

07:44.630 --> 07:47.133
<i>I</i> have more work
for your teacher.

07:47.216 --> 07:48.384
She left forever.

07:48.467 --> 07:49.594
Left forever?!

07:49.677 --> 07:51.721
If she's gone,
then who will I dump

07:51.804 --> 07:54.307
all aspects
of education policy on?

07:54.390 --> 07:57.351
I gotta get her back!
[ Engine revs ]

07:57.435 --> 08:00.396
This isn't relaxing
at all.

08:00.479 --> 08:02.398
-Phew.
<i>-Teacher Terry!</i>

08:02.481 --> 08:05.234
<i>This is the government!</i>
<i>We're out to get you!</i>

08:05.318 --> 08:07.612
Huh?
Aaaaah!

08:07.695 --> 08:09.530
There I was,
minding my own business --

08:09.614 --> 08:12.116
Teacher Terry: Aaah!
[ Horn honks ]

08:12.200 --> 08:15.411
It appears Teacher Terry
has lost it.

08:15.494 --> 08:16.913
[ Gasps ]

08:16.996 --> 08:19.999
This could affect my Claudette's
educational progress.

08:21.459 --> 08:22.960
Teacher Terry, a word!

08:23.044 --> 08:24.921
Coach Croach: They make it look
so easy in the book.

08:25.004 --> 08:28.925
Hey, Coach Croach,
Teacher Terry's skipping town.

08:29.008 --> 08:31.677
Teacher Terry:
You can't make me go back!

08:31.761 --> 08:32.887
Oh! She can't leave!

08:32.970 --> 08:34.805
I'll have to keep
teaching forever!

08:34.889 --> 08:36.432
Hey!
Teacher Terry!

08:36.515 --> 08:38.851
Come take your class back!

08:38.935 --> 08:40.686
Aaaaaaah!

08:40.770 --> 08:41.896
Aaah!

08:41.979 --> 08:44.190
Aaaah! Aaaah!

08:44.273 --> 08:45.775
[ Horns honking ]

08:45.858 --> 08:47.526
Aaaah!

08:47.610 --> 08:49.528
How do we stop
Teacher Terry?

08:49.612 --> 08:50.947
Slash her tires?

08:51.030 --> 08:53.115
No, I don't think
that'll work.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.825
[ Sighs ]
Look how miserable she is.

08:54.909 --> 08:58.579
[ Horns honking ]
Teacher Terry!
Come back here!

08:58.663 --> 09:00.915
Forcing her to stay here
just for us --

09:00.998 --> 09:02.375
it's wrong.
Let me go! Let me go!

09:02.458 --> 09:05.461
It's time we set
our teacher free.
Ah!

09:05.544 --> 09:07.421
Oh, no!
What do I do?

09:07.505 --> 09:10.466
Free boat! Yep.
Right here!

09:10.549 --> 09:11.467
There!

09:11.550 --> 09:12.843
Take it
if you want it.

09:12.927 --> 09:14.303
I don't care.

09:14.387 --> 09:15.429
Yes!

09:15.513 --> 09:17.431
She's going for
the free boat!

09:17.515 --> 09:20.643
I got her! Ha!

09:20.726 --> 09:22.103
[ Gasps ] No!

09:22.186 --> 09:23.479
Nice arm, Mayor!

09:23.562 --> 09:25.731
Heave!
All: Hooo!

09:25.815 --> 09:28.150
Heave!
Hooo!

09:28.234 --> 09:30.027
[ Grunting ]

09:30.111 --> 09:32.780
That's right, Teacher Terry,
back to your duties.

09:32.863 --> 09:34.115
[ Bang! ]
Aah!

09:34.198 --> 09:35.658
-Wheee!
-Ow!

09:35.741 --> 09:36.951
Huh?

09:37.034 --> 09:38.494
Fire in the Holk.

09:38.577 --> 09:39.787
[ Bang! ]

09:39.870 --> 09:41.372
Uh-oh. Aah!

09:41.455 --> 09:43.124
Get it off, get it off!

09:43.207 --> 09:45.710
Oof!
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa! ♪

09:45.793 --> 09:47.336
[ Laughing wildly ]

09:47.420 --> 09:50.131
♪ Maybe I just want,
maybe I just want to relax ♪

09:50.214 --> 09:52.091
♪ Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! ♪

09:52.174 --> 09:53.217
Aw, phooey.

09:53.301 --> 09:55.469
Fare thee well,
Teacher Terry.

09:55.553 --> 09:59.015
[ Laughing ]
See you later, suckers!

09:59.098 --> 10:02.184
♪♪

10:02.268 --> 10:05.354
Got it. And there.

10:05.438 --> 10:07.481
A perfect pentagon.

10:07.565 --> 10:09.608
That's a hexagon.

10:09.692 --> 10:12.361
Ah, darn it.
Ah, okay.

10:12.445 --> 10:14.030
I'll get it this time.

10:14.113 --> 10:15.323
Hey!

10:15.406 --> 10:18.576
Remember that time you chased
our teacher out of town?

10:18.659 --> 10:20.369
If Teacher Terry needed
to leave,

10:20.453 --> 10:22.163
we have to respect
her decision.

10:22.246 --> 10:25.374
But we will adapt,
and we will survive.

10:25.458 --> 10:27.043
Guess who's back.

10:27.126 --> 10:29.378
All: Teacher Terry!

10:29.462 --> 10:30.546
Whazza -- what now?

10:30.629 --> 10:32.214
We thought
you'd left forever.

10:32.298 --> 10:35.051
Oh, I would never
leave my class.

10:35.134 --> 10:37.678
I spent some time at
Sharon Carpenter's lake house

10:37.762 --> 10:39.096
to clear my head.

10:39.180 --> 10:40.598
I guess
when you're overwhelmed,

10:40.681 --> 10:42.600
it makes sense
to take the time you need

10:42.683 --> 10:45.061
to feel better
and not rush it.

10:45.144 --> 10:46.354
Exactly.

10:46.437 --> 10:48.564
Now I'm back and ready
to give it my all.

10:48.647 --> 10:51.525
We don't need<i> all</i> of you,
Teacher Terry.

10:51.609 --> 10:53.652
You should save some time
for yourself.

10:53.736 --> 10:56.405
But do you think
you could handle a hug?

10:56.489 --> 10:57.823
Of course!

10:57.907 --> 11:01.035
-We love you Teacher Terry!
-We missed you!

11:01.118 --> 11:02.745
[ Whistle! ]
Holk, no!

11:02.828 --> 11:03.871
[ Crash! ]

11:03.954 --> 11:05.456
[ All grunting ]

11:06.332 --> 11:12.213
♪♪

11:12.296 --> 11:18.177
♪♪

11:18.260 --> 11:20.304
Ahhh!
